1046:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
1047:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (++) Blocking mode : The communication is performed in the polling mode.
1048:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****             The status of all data processing is returned by the same function
1049:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****             after finishing transfer.
1050:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (++) No-Blocking mode : The communication is performed using Interrupts
1051:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****             or DMA. These functions return the status of the transfer startup.
1052:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****             The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
1053:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****             dedicated I2C IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when
1054:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****             using DMA mode.
1055:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c **** 
1056:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_i2c.c ****     (#) Blocking mode functions are :
